==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glycose
<hw>Gly"cose</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ sweet +
<ets>-ose</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a class
of carbohydrates having from three to nine atoms of carbon in the
molecules and having the constitution either of an aldehyde alcohol or
of a ketone alcohol. Most glycoses have hydrogen and oxygen present in
the proportion to form water, while the number of carbon atoms is
usually equal to the number of atoms of oxygen.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glycosine</ent>⟦br⟧
